citations:
    citation-agot-catelyn-vi:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Catelyn VI"
            text_from_source: "Stone was a bastard's name in the Vale, as Snow was in the north, and Flowers in Highgarden; in each of the Seven Kingdoms, custom had fashioned a surname for children born with no names of their own."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Catelyn arrives at the Bloody Gate with Tyrion as prisoner. Reunites with her uncle Brynden Tully (the Blackfish), Knight of the Gate. Met by Ser Donnel Waynwood and Lord Nestor Royce. Mya Stone guides Catelyn up the mountain by night to the Eyrie. Catelyn meets Lysa Arryn and young Robert Arryn."
